These instructions are for the AI agent.

Update this file with a preceding "[x]" before each instruction if you believe you have implemented it, and include it as a claim in the documentation to be tested. 

Uncheck "[x]" before each instruction if you believe you have not implemented it or if it is no longer satisfied.

Ensure that the project is well-documented and easy to understand.

Ensure that the project is well-tested and easy to maintain.

Documentation claims should have a minimum of one corresponding test.

The test and the claim should be cross-referenced. 

No feature will prevent specific keypresses from reaching focused text input controls.  


Claims should be supported in the documentation by references to code filenames, functions, constants, variables, etc.

Ensure that these instructions are followed and that the project is updated accordingly.



core/faceOrientationKeyMapping should not be modified without express approval.

core/faceOrientationKeyMapping.ts is a critical file that maps the face orientation to the key mapping.

It also can be used to determine the orientation of the next dominant face.

Understand that I refer to a "face" I am referring to one of the 24 possible orientations of the cube.



